description._content: Image Description from historic lecture booklet: "Population, 780, 220. Naples is the largest city in Italy. It is located near a fertile lowland where a very dense population is supported. the climate is warm in this lowland area, and most of the people lead an agricultural life. Nearly all the inhabitants of this region make their homes in the villages near the coast and go into the country each day to work on their farms."
